import and libraries

First import all raw data. The concentrations of P, Fe and Mn in the extraction solutions, and the Dryweight data.

concdata <- read_xlsx("20220800SequentalExtractions.xlsx")
beforedata <- read_xlsx("20220600SequentialExtractions.xlsx")
wtdata <- read_xlsx("20220816_AR_Dryweight.xlsx")

kwadata <- read_xlsx("KWA.xlsx")

Total elements

kwa <- kwadata %>% 
  filter(!is.na(depth)) %>% 
  mutate_at(5:21, ~ (.*0.05)/weight) %>% 
  group_by(ID) %>% 
  summarise_all(mean)

kwabefore <- kwadata %>% 
  filter(ID == "before") %>% 
  mutate_at(5:21, ~ (.*0.05)/weight) %>% 
  select( c(ID, depth, Al, Ca, Fe, K, Mg, Mn, Na, P, Pb, S, Ti)) %>%  mutate(FeP = Fe/P)
kwalong <- select(kwa, c(ID, depth, Al, Ca, Fe, K, Mg, Mn, Na, P, Pb, S, Ti)) %>% 
  mutate(FeP = Fe/P) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = 3:last_col(), names_to = "Parameter", values_to = "Value")

kwaplots <- ggplot(  kwalong, 
         mapping = aes(
           y = Value,
           x = depth,
          color = Parameter)
) +
   
  geom_line()  +
  geom_point(size = 2) +
  facet_grid(cols = vars(Parameter), scales = "free") +
  geom_point( data = pivot_longer(kwabefore, cols = 3:last_col(), names_to = "Parameter", values_to = "Value") , aes( y = Value, x = 0),color="black")+

  xlab("Depth (cm)") +
  scale_x_reverse() +
  coord_flip() +
  labs(  y = expression(paste("concentration mg/g")), 
         x = "Depth in cm",
         title = "element profiles" ) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(      aspect.ratio = 2,
                  axis.title=element_text(size=8),
                  plot.title = element_text(size=20, face="bold", hjust = 0.5) ,
                  axis.text=element_text(size=8,angle = 0, hjust = 0.5),
                  legend.title = element_text(size = 8),
                  legend.text = element_text(size = 8),
                  legend.key.size = unit(1.5, "cm"))

Sequential Extractions

Data Corrections

Filter the values of the blanks from the concentration data, and take the mean value for each measurement series.

blanks <- filter(concdata, is.na(Depth)) %>% 
  group_by(Fraction, Parameter, Measurement) %>%
  summarise(blank = mean(Conc), .groups = "drop") 

beforeblanks <- filter(beforedata, is.na(Depth)) %>% 
  group_by(Fraction, Parameter) %>%
  summarise(blank = mean(Conc), .groups = "drop")

Define porosity values for all measurements

porosity <- data.frame(
  porosity = rep(c(pull(
    wtdata %>% group_by(Sample) %>% summarise(porosity = mean(Porosity)), porosity),0),each = 2,times = 26)
  )

beforeporosity <-  pull(
    beforedata %>% filter(Parameter == "porosity") %>% summarise(porosity = mean(Conc)), porosity)

Compute percentage dryweight from volume of solution and porosity

conc <- concdata %>% 
  bind_cols(porosity) %>% 
  left_join(blanks, by = c("Fraction","Parameter","Measurement")) %>% 
  mutate(volume = case_when(
    Fraction == "H2O" ~ 0.05,
    Fraction == "Bipy" | Fraction == "BD" ~ 0.1,
    Fraction == "NaOH" ~ 0.075,
    T ~ 0 )) %>%  
  mutate(cont = ((Conc-blank)*volume)/(Weight*(1-porosity)))

before <- beforedata %>% remove_missing() %>%  left_join(beforeblanks, by = c("Fraction","Parameter")) %>% 
  mutate(volume = case_when(
    Nr == "5"~ 0.150,
    Fraction == "H2O" ~ 0.05,
    Fraction == "Bipy" | Fraction == "BD" ~ 0.1,
    Fraction == "NaOH" ~ 0.075,
    T ~ 0 )) %>%  
  mutate(cont = (((Conc*2)-blank)*volume)/(Weight*(1-beforeporosity)))
## Warning: Removed 35 rows containing missing values.
beforevalues <- before %>%   
  filter( Parameter == "TP" | Parameter == "SRP" ) %>% 
  mutate( Fraction = paste(Fraction, Parameter) ) %>% 
  group_by( Fraction) %>% 
  summarise( stdev = sd(cont), cont = mean(cont) ) %>% 
  add_row(Fraction = "Total", stdev = 0, cont = pull(  
  summarise_all(group_by(kwabefore, ID), mean), "P"))
Pdata <- filter(remove_missing(conc), (Parameter == "TP" | Parameter == "SRP") & Fraction != "BD")
## Warning: Removed 124 rows containing missing values.
Pdata$Fraction <- factor(Pdata$Fraction)
summary(lm( cont ~ Weight, data = Pdata[Pdata$Fraction == "Bipy",] ))

Analyze Bipy measurements

Filter and group bipy data by measurement type (acidified or not, TP or SRP) and avarage for each depth.

bipy <- filter(conc, Fraction == "Bipy" ) %>%  
  filter( Parameter == "TP" | Parameter == "SRP" ) %>% 
  remove_missing() %>% 
  mutate(Parameter = case_when(
    Parameter == "TP" & Measurement <= 4 ~ "TPnoacid",
    Parameter == "TP" & Measurement >= 9 ~ "TP block",
    Parameter == "TP" & Measurement > 4 & Measurement < 9 ~ "TPacidified",
    T ~ "SRP"
    )) %>% 
  group_by(Parameter,  Depth) %>% 
  summarise(stdev = sd(cont), cont = mean(cont) ) 
## Warning: Removed 23 rows containing missing values.
bipytot <- filter(conc, Fraction == "Bipy" ) %>%  
  filter( (Parameter == "TP" & Measurement >4 )| Parameter == "SRP" ) %>% 
  remove_missing() %>% 
  group_by( Depth) %>% 
  summarise(stdev = sd(cont), cont = mean(cont) ) 
## Warning: Removed 14 rows containing missing values.

## Plot of the P sequentiallly extracted.

Define the P fractions: Select only the P measurements without blanks. For Bipy only the acidified measurements were taken.

Pkwa <- select(kwa, depth, P) %>% 
  mutate(Fraction = "Total", stdev = 0) %>% 
  rename(Depth = depth, cont = P)

allfrac <- conc %>% filter(Parameter == "TP" | Parameter == "SRP") %>% 
  mutate(Fraction = case_when(
    Fraction == "Bipy" && Parameter == "TP" && Measurement <= 4 ~ NA_character_,
    Fraction == "Bipy" ~ "Bipy TP",
    T ~ paste(Fraction, Parameter)
                              )) %>%  
  remove_missing() %>% 
  group_by(Fraction,  Depth) %>% 
  summarise(stdev = sd(cont), cont = mean(cont) ) %>% ungroup() %>% 
  bind_rows(mutate(filter(beforevalues, Fraction != "Bipy SRP"), Depth = 48)) %>% 
  bind_rows(Pkwa) 
## Warning in Fraction == "Bipy" && Parameter == "TP": 'length(x) = 526 > 1' in
## coercion to 'logical(1)'
## Warning: Removed 38 rows containing missing values.

Only the TP fractions.

tpfrac <- allfrac %>% filter(str_detect(Fraction, "TP"))

The NRP is calculated forNaOH, by subtracting the SRP from the TP.

mutfrac <- bind_cols(
  rename(
    filter( allfrac, Fraction == "NaOH TP" ), TP = cont),
  select( rename(
    filter( allfrac, Fraction == "NaOH SRP" ), SRP = cont), SRP) 
  ) %>%  
  mutate(cont = TP-SRP) %>% 
  select(Fraction,Depth,cont) %>% 
  bind_rows(select(filter(allfrac, Fraction != "NaOH TP" & Fraction != "H2O SRP"), !stdev)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = Fraction, values_from = cont) %>% 
  mutate(Total = Total - .data[["H2O TP"]]- .data[["Bipy TP"]]- .data[["BD TP"]]- .data[["NaOH TP"]]- .data[["NaOH SRP"]]) %>% 
  pivot_longer(2:7, names_to = "Fraction", values_to = "cont")
